  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.6.1`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nAccording to the documentation of the [eth_newFilter](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JSON-RPC#eth_newfilter) RPC call, the `fromBlock` and `toBlock` fields default to `\"latest\"` if left empty. This was working up to geth 1.6.0.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nWith geth `1.6.1` a call to the client with empty block fields will produce an error instead of defaulting to `\"latest\"`.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nJust an example RPC call with the error:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl localhost:29871 -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\", \"method\": \"eth_newFilter\", \"params\": [{\"fromBlock\": \"\", \"address\": \"0x29d73fd964f1d5a9b2ba668c4ac31c61744a1b21\", \"topics\": [\"0xdffbd9ded1c09446f09377de547142dcce7d c541c8b0b028142b1eba7026b9e7\"], \"toBlock\": \"\"}], \"id\": 229}'\r\n```\r\n\r\nwill produce the following error:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":229,\"error\":{\"code\":-32602,\"message\":\"invalid argument 0: empty hex string\"}}\r\n```",
